House Prices Prediction with DNN Regression¶

The aim of this project is to build a Deep Neural Netowork to predict the housing prices in Boston using the Boston Housing dataset which has 79 features some of which are: Overall material and finish quality, The building class, Above grade (ground) living area square feet etc.

The data was acquired from Kaggle.

The GitHub repository for this project can be found here.

Impute categorical values¶

To impute categorical values we should first encode them.

In [9]:
# find numerical features
df_cat = df.select_dtypes(exclude = [np.number])
In [10]:
cat_pipeline = Pipeline([
    ('imputer', SimpleImputer(strategy='most_frequent')),
    ('encoder', OneHotEncoder(handle_unknown='ignore', sparse=False)),
    ])
In [11]:
X_cat = cat_pipeline.fit_transform(df_cat)
In [12]:
column_name = cat_pipeline['encoder'].get_feature_names(df_cat.columns)
df_cat_tr =  pd.DataFrame(X_cat, columns=column_name)

Merge the transformed numerical and categorical values¶

In [13]:
df_tr = pd.merge(df_num_tr, df_cat_tr, left_index=True, right_index=True)

DNN Regression¶

In [131]:
def build_and_compile_model(norm):
  model = keras.Sequential([
      norm,
      layers.Dense(64, activation='relu'),
      layers.Dense(64, activation='relu'),
      layers.Dense(1)
  ])

  model.compile(loss='mean_absolute_error',
                optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(0.001))
  return model
